>This happened to me, too. The kids and I were leaving karate class,
>drove up the steep driveway, made the switchback, revved the engine...
>The right mount broke, the engine was dragging on the ground racing
>because the throttle cable was stretched tight.
>
>Turned off the key right away. Assessed the problem, got the jack out
>and set the right end of the mustache bar back in place and secured it
>with several tie wraps, then drove it (VERY gingerly!) 44 miles home.
>Fixed it properly the next day.
